---
import CodeBlock from "./CodeBlock.astro";
import docs from "../../data/docs.json";
---

<section id="cli">
  <h2>Command line</h2>
  <p>The app bundle ships a companion CLI at <code>Contents/Helpers/junction</code> (Homebrew links it onto your PATH automatically).</p>
  <CodeBlock title="Terminal">
    {docs.cliCommands.map((c, i) => (
      <Fragment>
        {i > 0 && "\n"}<span class="tk-cmd">{c.command}</span>{c.arg}{" ".repeat(Math.max(1, 48 - c.command.length - c.arg.length))}<span class="tk-cmt">{c.comment}</span>
      </Fragment>
    ))}
  </CodeBlock>
  <p><code>junction test</code> is the fastest way to reason about precedence — it prints which rule matched and what Junction would do, without opening anything. Add <code>--source &lt;bundle-id&gt;</code> to test a source-app rule:</p>
  <CodeBlock title="Terminal">
    <span class="tk-cmd">junction test</span> "https://mycorp.atlassian.net/browse/X-1" --source com.tinyspeck.slackmacgap
  </CodeBlock>
  <p><code>junction config validate</code> runs the same validation the GUI and the file watcher use, so a config that passes here is a config the app will load.</p>
</section>
